  "title": "Hits widget should support table as a valid container",
  "body": "Here is my hits widget:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(                                                                  \n  instantsearch.widgets.hits({                                                     \n    container: '#donations',                                                       \n    templates: {                                                                   \n      item: '<tr><td>{{created_at}}</td><td>${{gross_amount}} {{donor}}</td></tr>' \n    }                                                                              \n  })                                                                               \n);                                                                                 \n```\n\nMy markup:\n\n``` html\n<table id=\"donations\" class=\"table table-striped table-condensed\"></table> \n```\n\nApparently this code is not valid and I get this error message in the console:\n`Warning: validateDOMNesting(...): <div> cannot appear as a child of <table>. See table > Hits > div.`\n\nIs it possible to use a `table` element as a container for hits?\n",
